Mine is different, mages are not all about &quot;power&quot; or damage in the high end. We evolve into what we're meant to be... Summoners. <br>
<br>
<br>
Whats the most talked about thing in the high end game? Bigger mobs mostly.... loot... and doing the stuff that the big shots do. <br>
<br>
High end = raids. The damage is all done by rogues, wizards, warriors.. etc. Everybody does a little bit, but the guys who get nothing else, except damage.... do their damage job very well. <br>
<br>
Our little niche is summoning. Some people don't like the idea that we summon rods and drop them on the ground for an armada of clerics to devour soon as they can spend enough mana for one, but look at it this way... Who else is gonna do it? We're called Conjurers... Summoners.. and Arch Mages, because thats what we do. <br>
<br>
We grew up with damage true... we got alot of summons as well, useless, but we got them to give us an idea of what else we can do. Shaman's first nuke was fire based.... know that shaman have 1 Fire based nuke still, the lvl 1 nuke for 4 dmg... do you think they are whining right now for better fire nukes? <br>
<br>
Rods can make or break a raid whether you wanna admit it or not. We're essential to raids and Mages stack well. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaamilae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aamilae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 402<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 8:15:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=335.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: high end?</span><hr size=1> Call it what you will, technically it's an opinion based on facts.<br>
<br>
The point that remains is that no class aside from magicians completely changes their role from a normal experience group to raiding.  Examples:<br>
<br>
* Clerics will still heal;<br>
* Shamans and Druids will still buff, heal and do some damage;<br>
* Melee will melee; etc.<br>
<br>
Magicians were pre-kunark damage dealers in groups but in the &quot;end-game&quot; (yes guys, even pre-kunark) magicians failed to be as useful as they were in groups on a raid.  In fact, it was raids pre-kunark that introduced me to the role of rod summoner.  In groups as a magician I was a damage dealer.  Why?<br>
<br>
The end-game was a couple planes and two dragons.  Pets on dragon raids were useless since the majority of the pets time was spent feared as we had no form of valient companion, and infact pets were useless on any mob that feared until you're 59 -- for the most part.<br>
<br>
Our nukes on most end-game boss mobs were inferior and resisted more often than wizards.  I don't know about you guys but I could never land a Shock of Sword on Nagafen, never happened.<br>
<br>
Kunark just extended an already terrible end-game for Magicians into the everyday grouping situation by watering down our post-50 pets and diminishing our relative nuking power, aside from the obvious raise in the resistance by boss mobs. Kunark was better at 60 than it was at any previous level though, and I was finally able to nuke reliably on dragons such as Trakanon, Severilous and Goreianaire (sp?).<br>
<br>
Velious continued with that theme initially, as was mentioned, with even the green-to-60 mobs being almost entirely resistant to even our fire based nukes.  Who'd of thunk a golem of velium would resist seering flames, I guess they weren't hot enough.  After quite a few months that did change and life in Velious became bearable.<br>
<br>
I still don't have the last pet heal, but I really love the lower-50 pet heal from Luclin.  Other than that the addition of a fire-based, conjuration nuke was nice -- even though it did less damage than the fire bolt we already had.  My only reservation with Luclin really revolves around our rather poorly upgraded spells spanning from pre-Kunark to recent history, mobs -- even experience mobs, have so many hitpoints and our nukes are still fairly pre-kunark level and damage  (consider that our currently best bolt has still only been upgrades 224 damage in three expansions and something might seem just a tad off, eh?).<br>
<br>
I summary I'd like to get everyone to focus on the single fact that magicians who group and magicians who participate in the &quot;end-game&quot; play two entirely different games.  Why?  No other class plays two entirely different games from start and then only at the end.  I will put forward that my opinion is that it's simply because Verant has not grown our class like they have others, and this is the very reason we're were we are today.<br>
<br>
Aamilae Banadar<br>
60 Magician, Xev<br>
Played since Beta 3, as a magician.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udumonyu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dumonyu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 9:56:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=335.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Well...</span><hr size=1> I pretty much totally agree with the original post. The gist of it is right on the money.<br>
<br>
People who joined up post Kunark don't seem appreciate the de-evolution of mages. MOB hp has gone through the roof compared to days of old, and the fact that players got MASSIVE gear upgrades with every expansion making them near Godlike, while pets got MINIMAL enhancements has throw our class completely out of whack. Nothing has affected us more than this, and if it's not fixed, we will never recover.<br>
<br>
Pre-Kunark the PvP melee players bitched because Mages and Necros were so strong (forget the fact that melees are about 1000x easier to play) and I mean they bitched HARD. Hard enough that Verant listened, even though PvP is a tiny part of the playing populace, and  Mages have never recovered from that attempt to balance PvP. But gee...what about balance vs MOBs. Isn't that what 90% of us have to worry about?<br>
<br>
Verant needs to rethink where they have taken mages and for gods sake bump up the damn pets. And I don't mean this 5% bullshit either. Either triple the damage, or triple the HP. Period.<br>
<br>
Pre Kunark I could solo 50 wars with only my pet without breaking a sweat. <br>
(this with a 49 pet) <br>
While this infuriated Wars, a pet will NEVER replace a group or a raids need for a tank, and I think that level of pet power was justified. After all there are MAJOR drawbacks to having to rely on a pet to do your fighting for you. Most people at that time were STILL turned off by pets, even though they rocked, because of the added danger a pet brought to a group, AND they took xp! (also if you went LD your pet tended to kick all your friends asses) And let's not forget the 1000x your pet broke mez while you struggled to control it, or trained the group after discovering yet ANOTHER pathing bug, all on it's own. Remember...<br>
&quot;Has anyone seen Jabober?&quot;<br>
LOADING...PLEASE WAIT<br>
<br>
I saw a guy post something about &quot;mages are becoming what they are supposed to be...summoners&quot; Please understand my rage when I think about this. While it sounds nice and pat, us being summoners and all, the reality is NO ONE plays EQ to be a walking store and if you started your Mage after this change took place, I can't imagine how you thought this would be fun. Mages were about DAMAGE and solo ability. I can remember players being in AWE of my ability to solo MOBs. Now we are down on the bottom of that list too. /golf clap Verant<br>
<br>
It used to be a tough but rewarding class to play compared to many others, but now there seems to be little reward. EVERY casting class basically has comparable nukes. Pets are no longer unique. The only desirable unique quality Mages have now is Coth and rods. What a letdown. I wish I could take all the n00b Mages back in time and show them what it used to be like to be a Mage, what I did during my average gaming session, and maybe they would understand my frustration.<br>
<br>
In summary: If PoP doesn't bring something to the Mage table, I think I'm going to finally bail on a character and game I've been playing since '99. Our nukes are no better than any other casting class, (even enc for christ sake) pet are right at useless, and I just can't stand the thought of staring at a wall making the 10 millionth rod for a PoP raid, when I can barely get an xp group to get my useless aa abilities because everyone knows that it's almost ALWAYS better to have anything but a MAG.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
